The paper deals with auction mechanisms and their approximation guarantees for revenue and welfare maximization in settings where agents have a common budget. This falls under the domain of computational game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic mechanism design (cs.EC). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) to design the auction mechanisms. The use of envy-free benchmarks and the characterization of optimal outcomes suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of approximation guarantees, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
